## Phase 6 — Determine pass/fail and archive the run to the mcp-dashboard repo

**Pass condition (ALL of the following must hold):**
- Phase 3 gate PASS (no skill_execution_error)
- All `required_calls` invariants PASS
- All `forbidden_calls` invariants PASS
- `mission_match` score ≥ 3

A 5/5 judge score with an invariant FAIL is still a FAIL (Deadly Sin #4).
An invariant PASS with `mission_match` < 3 is still a FAIL.

**Persistence — the durable home is the `leadbay/mcp-dashboard` repo, not the worktree.**
Eval runs are committed to `mcp-dashboard/evals/` (one JSON per `/eval` invocation,
EvalEntry-compatible — schema in that repo's `evals/README.md`). This is the
shared, version-controlled history that survives Conductor worktree cleanup and
is read by the hosted dashboard at `/evals`. The old per-worktree
`$REPO_ROOT/.context/evals/` is now only a **local fallback** when the dashboard
repo isn't checked out.

**Logging rule — write every result immediately, every time:**
Every eval session result — including `--improve` relentless iterations and
`--verify` stability rounds — is written as soon as it completes. Do NOT batch
at the end.

- Each `/eval` invocation gets its own timestamped JSON file written immediately.
- `--improve` iterations: tag each entry `"suite": "relentless"`, `"_relentless_iter": N`, `"_relentless_goal": "..."`.
- `--verify` rounds: tag `"suite": "verify"`, `"_verify_round": N`.
- A plain `/eval` run uses `"suite": "eval"`.

```bash
# Resolve the mcp-dashboard checkout. Prefer an env override, then the
# conventional sibling clone, then a fresh shallow clone into a cache dir.
# Fall back to the worktree-local .context/evals only if all of that fails
# (e.g. offline) — that copy is ephemeral and NOT shared.
DASH_REPO="${LEADBAY_MCP_DASHBOARD_DIR:-}"
for cand in "$DASH_REPO" "$HOME/Leadbay/mcp-dashboard" "$HOME/leadbay/mcp-dashboard"; do
  [ -n "$cand" ] && [ -d "$cand/.git" ] && DASH_REPO="$cand" && break
done
if [ -z "$DASH_REPO" ] || [ ! -d "$DASH_REPO/.git" ]; then
  DASH_REPO="${LEADBAY_HOME:-$HOME/.leadbay}/mcp-dashboard"
  if [ ! -d "$DASH_REPO/.git" ]; then
    git clone --depth 1 git@github.com:leadbay/mcp-dashboard.git "$DASH_REPO" 2>/dev/null \
      || git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/leadbay/mcp-dashboard.git "$DASH_REPO" 2>/dev/null || true
  fi
fi

if [ -d "$DASH_REPO/.git" ]; then
  git -C "$DASH_REPO" pull -q --ff-only 2>/dev/null || true
  EVALS_DIR="$DASH_REPO/evals"
  ARCHIVE_TO_DASHBOARD=1
else
  echo "WARN: mcp-dashboard repo not available — falling back to local .context/evals (not shared)"
  EVALS_DIR="$REPO_ROOT/.context/evals"
  ARCHIVE_TO_DASHBOARD=0
fi
mkdir -p "$EVALS_DIR"

# Filename: ISO timestamp + the workflow ids this run covered (e.g. wf25-26-27).
RUN_ID=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H-%M-%S)
WF_TAG="wf$(echo "$WORKFLOW_IDS" | tr ',' '-')"   # WORKFLOW_IDS from Phase 0
RESULT_FILE="$EVALS_DIR/${RUN_ID}_${WF_TAG}.json"
echo "Saving to: $RESULT_FILE  (archive_to_dashboard=$ARCHIVE_TO_DASHBOARD)"
```

The run file is the wrapped archive shape from `mcp-dashboard/evals/README.md`
(`schema_version`, `generated_at`, `skill_version`, `git`, `summary`, `entries[]`).
Each element of `entries[]` follows the `EvalEntry` schema:
```json
{
  "name": "PROMPT_NAME/workflow-N",
  "suite": "eval",
  "tier": "t3",
  "touchfile_reason": "eval-skill",
  "passed": true,
  "exit_reason": "agent_stopped",
  "duration_ms": 0,
  "cost_usd_session": 0,
  "cost_usd_judges": 0,
  "tokens_session_in": 0,
  "tokens_session_cache": 0,
  "tokens_session_out": 0,
  "tokens_judge_in": 0,
  "tokens_judge_out": 0,
  "turns_used": 0,
  "tool_call_count": 0,
  "tool_call_breakdown": {},
  "shape_ratio": 0,
  "first_response_ms": 0,
  "max_inter_turn_ms": 0,
  "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
  "evidence": {
    "session": {
      "session_id": "RUN_ID-workflow-N",
      "prompt_name": "PROMPT_NAME",
      "fixture_id": "workflow-N",
      "terminal_reason": "agent_stopped"
    },
    "tool_calls": [],
    "prose_between_tool_calls": [],
    "final_agent_message": "...",
    "turns": [],
    "invariants": [],
    "judge_scores": {},
    "judge_reasoning": "...",
    "per_criterion": []
  }
}
```

**Commit + push the run to the dashboard repo** (only when `ARCHIVE_TO_DASHBOARD=1`).
This is what makes history shared and durable — mirror how `/mcp-analysis`
archives into the same repo. Commit only the JSON (and optional `.md` scorecard);
never the generated `*.html` (gitignored).

```bash
if [ "$ARCHIVE_TO_DASHBOARD" = "1" ]; then
  git -C "$DASH_REPO" add "evals/$(basename "$RESULT_FILE")" 2>/dev/null
  # include a sibling .md scorecard if you wrote one
  [ -f "${RESULT_FILE%.json}.md" ] && git -C "$DASH_REPO" add "evals/$(basename "${RESULT_FILE%.json}.md")"
  if ! git -C "$DASH_REPO" diff --cached --quiet; then
    git -C "$DASH_REPO" commit -q -m "evals: ${RUN_ID} ${WF_TAG} — $(echo "$SUMMARY_LINE")" \
      && git -C "$DASH_REPO" push -q 2>/dev/null \
      && echo "archived + pushed run to mcp-dashboard/evals/" \
      || echo "WARN: committed locally but push failed — run 'git -C $DASH_REPO push' later"
  fi
fi
```

`SUMMARY_LINE` is a one-liner like `3/3 passed (wf25-27)`. If the push fails
(offline / no creds), the commit is still local in the dashboard clone — report
it as DONE_WITH_CONCERNS and tell the user to push it.

